      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SILVER TOP RIDGE (8) went close last start over 1200m at Seymour. That followed an all-the-way Maiden win at Wangaratta. Keeps improving and Meech will position forward. Tumbles in weight and that brings her right into it. CHARMED RUN (1) also hits this at peak and wasn't far away a month ago in a 78 at Caulfield Heath. Carries clear top weight but will be belting home over the longer sprint. A serious player. BEFORE THE WAR (3) improved last time out to score by a nose over 1209m at Yarra Valley. Must raise the bar but deserves consideration on an each-way basis. GOT OUT THE FENCE (5) is a leader seeking the hat-trick in stronger. Gets in light and is on an eight-day return. Can't be ruled out. SNAPPY TYCOON (4) went well at Kyneton last time and won't be far away.",
